On March 18, WHO announced that chloroquine and related hydroxychloroquine would be among the four drugs to be studied in the Solidarity clinical trial.
New York Governor Andrew Cuomo announced that New York State trials with chloroquine and hydroxichloroquine would begin on March 24. On March 28, the FDA authorized the use of hydroxichloroquine sulphate and chloroquine phosphate through an urgent use authorisation (US).
