Chinese clinical trials in Wuhan and Shenzhen stated that favipiravir was "clearly effective."
Thirty-five patients in Shenzhen gave negative in an average of 4 days, while the duration of the disease was 11 days in 45 patients who did not receive it.
In a study in Wuhan in 240 patients with pneumonia, half received favipiravir, while the other half were given umifenovir.
